message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in São Tomé and Príncipe in the past 5 years was the presidential election held in July 2016. This election marked a peaceful transition of power and brought a new president to the country. Evaristo Carvalho, the candidate supported by the ruling party, won the election and became the President of São Tomé and Príncipe. This event was significant as it demonstrated the country's commitment to democracy and political stability.
